	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=308688><span id= >Sephiris</span></a><br><span id=notbold>7 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The cost to make one of these depends on where you get the gem. The prices on drop only items vary from server to server so I cannot vouch for others, but I've seen desperate players pay up to 1kpp for a black sapphire. If you happen to find one of these at a vendor, it'll run you roughly 230pp&nbsp;&nbsp;with 110cha or higher. The platinum bar costs 105pp with 110cha, but the cost to the jeweler to get the skill to make this a trivial item is enormous. I spent countless hours holed up in gem shops to get to 250jc skill-Thanks for the company Nyomy =). So it's really up to the jeweler as to what they charge. Make a chanter and start working on jewel crafting and you'll see what I mean about the cost. Have fun and bring a friend, it gets really lonely in those gem shops. By the way, these give you 55 endurance also nowadays.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Apr 17 19:16:51 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
